    {
        "content": "<ol>\n<li>is it possible to have Lando always use the latest Backdrop drush version from <a href=\"https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases\">https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases</a> (instead of us having to file PRs against <a href=\"https://github.com/lando/lando/blob/master/plugins/lando-recipes/recipes/backdrop/builder.js\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/lando/lando/blob/master/plugins/lando-recipes/recipes/backdrop/builder.js\">https://github.com/lando/lando/blob/master/plugins/lando-recipes/recipes/backdrop/builder.js</a>)</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases\" style=\"background-image: url(https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/7720679?s=400&amp;v=4)\" target=\"_blank\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"backdrop-contrib/drush\">backdrop-contrib/drush</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">A set of commands and boot class for Drush and Backdrop CMS. - backdrop-contrib/drush</div></div></div><div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/lando/lando/blob/master/plugins/lando-recipes/recipes/backdrop/builder.js\" style=\"background-image: url(https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/31605584?s=400&amp;v=4)\" target=\"_blank\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/lando/lando/blob/master/plugins/lando-recipes/recipes/backdrop/builder.js\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"lando/lando\">lando/lando</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">A local development and DevOps tool for all your projects that is fast, easy, powerful and liberating - lando/lando</div></div></div>",
        "id": 187748192,
        "sender_full_name": "klonos",
        "timestamp": 1581231685
    },
    {
        "content": "<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>How do I update my local version of Lando, to use the latest Backdrop recipe, w/o having to wait for the next official release of Lando?</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 187748194,
        "sender_full_name": "klonos",
        "timestamp": 1581231689
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You might be able to manually install it in the webroot under /drush. I haven't tried though. And that doesn't answer your question about the recipe</p>",
        "id": 187759855,
        "sender_full_name": "Herb",
        "timestamp": 1581256595
    },
    {
        "content": "<ol>\n<li>Yes; set the <code>backdrush: 1.x-1.x</code> in your<code>.lando.yml</code> file</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 187760869,
        "sender_full_name": "Geoff St. Pierre (serundeputy)",
        "timestamp": 1581258711
    },
    {
        "content": "<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Not really in any practical sense (you'd either have to hack lando our write your own custom plugin recipe)</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 187760921,
        "sender_full_name": "Geoff St. Pierre (serundeputy)",
        "timestamp": 1581258784
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I ended up doing something like this in the script I use:<br>\n<code>BACKDRUSH=\"$(curl -sL https://api.github.com/repos/backdrop-contrib/drush/releases/latest | jq -r '.tag_name')\"</code> ...and then <code>sed -i '' -e \"s/'?.?.?'/'${BACKDRUSH}'/g\" .lando.yml</code></p>",
        "id": 187768413,
        "sender_full_name": "klonos",
        "timestamp": 1581273752
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>^^ this grabs the latest tag from the (Backdrop) drush repo, and then sets its value in the .lando.yml file for me.</p>",
        "id": 187768432,
        "sender_full_name": "klonos",
        "timestamp": 1581273833
    },
    {
